# ============================================================================
# Large external data — keep only the directory placeholder (.gitkeep)
# These hold corpora, FAISS indexes, model weights and run outputs that are
# downloaded/generated locally and must NOT be committed (GitHub 100MB limit).
# ============================================================================
datasets/*
indexes/*
models/*
results/*
tests/*
webui_configs/*
!.gitkeep

# ============================================================================
# Experiment intermediate dumps
# `run_exp.py` writes one `intermediate_data.json` per experiment containing the
# retrieved documents, built prompts and raw generations for every sample.
# These are large (often >1GB each; ~31GB total here) and fully regenerable.
# We KEEP the small `config.yaml` + `metric_score.txt` next to them so the
# experiment setup and final metrics survive. See MIGRATION_NOTES.md.
# ============================================================================
**/intermediate_data.json

# ============================================================================
# Run logs (stdout dumps from run_exp.py — regenerable noise)
# ============================================================================
*.log

# ============================================================================
# Python / build artifacts
# ============================================================================
**/.history
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.egg-info
build/
dist/*
.idea/
upload_pypi.sh
